  "body": "## Simple Summary\r\nEnum in Vyper is modeled after enum Flag in Python.\r\n\r\nhttps://medium.com/@de33/enums-in-vyper-0-3-4-6ec2d387bc3a\r\n\r\nBut we don't support converting enum to boolean.\r\n\r\n\"Enums can be converted to and from uint256 only.\"\r\nhttps://docs.vyperlang.org/en/stable/types.html#type-conversions\r\n\r\n```python\r\nenum Roles:\r\n    ADMIN\r\n    USER\r\n\r\n@external\r\ndef foo():\r\n    a : Roles = Roles.ADMIN | Roles.USER\r\n    b : bool = convert(a, bool)\r\n```\r\n\r\nIt will throw an error:\r\n\r\n```bash\r\nError compiling: ../codevyper/converting_enum_to_bool.vy\r\nvyper.exceptions.TypeMismatch: Can't convert enum Roles('ADMIN','USER') to bool\r\n```\r\n\r\nBut in Python, it's possible to convert enum to bool.\r\n\r\n```python\r\nfrom enum import Flag, auto\r\n\r\nclass Color(Flag):\r\n\r\n    RED = auto()\r\n\r\n    GREEN = auto()\r\n\r\n    BLUE = auto()\r\n\r\na = Color.RED | Color.GREEN\r\nb = bool(a)\r\nprint(b)\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Motivation\r\n\r\nMake it more consistent with Python.\r\n\r\n## Specification\r\n\r\nIt should follow the Python enum flag boolean logic.\r\n\r\n```python\r\nfrom enum import Flag, auto\r\nclass Color(Flag):\r\n\r\n    RED = auto()\r\n\r\n    GREEN = auto()\r\n\r\n    BLUE = auto()\r\n```\r\n\r\n```python\r\n(Pdb) Color(0)\r\n<Color.0: 0>\r\n(Pdb) bool(Color(0))\r\nFalse\r\n(Pdb) bool(Color(1))\r\nTrue\r\n(Pdb) bool(Color(2))\r\nTrue\r\n(Pdb) bool(Color(3))\r\nTrue\r\n(Pdb) bool(Color(4))\r\nTrue\r\n(Pdb) bool(Color(5))\r\nTrue\r\n(Pdb) bool(Color(6))\r\nTrue\r\n(Pdb) bool(Color(7))\r\nTrue\r\n(Pdb) bool(Color(8))\r\n*** ValueError: 8 is not a valid Color\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\n## Backwards Compatibility\r\n\r\nIt's not backward compatible.\r\n\r\n## Dependencies\r\n\r\nNothing.\r\n\r\n## References\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/vyperlang/vyper/issues/3285\r\n\r\n## Copyright\r\nCopyright and related rights waived via [CC0](https://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/)\r\n",
